cppkafka
------------------------------------------
cppkafka allows C++ applications to consume and produce messages using the
Apache Kafka protocol. The library is built on top of librdkafka, and provides
a high level API that uses modern C++ features to make it easier to write code
while keeping the wrapper's performance overhead to a minimum.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.6-1
  libcppkafka-devel-0.3.1-1bl1
  libcppkafka0.3.1-0.3.1-1bl1
  libgcc1-11.3.0-1
  librdkafka-devel-1.9.2-1bl1
  librdkafka1-1.9.2-1bl1
  libstdc++6-11.3.0-1
  pkg-config-1.9.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.39-1
  cmake-3.23.2-1
  cygport-0.35.4-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.3.0-1
  librdkafka-devel-1.9.2-1bl1
  ninja-1.11.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/mfontanini/cppkafka

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/mfontanini/cppkafka/archive/refs/tags/v0.3.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack cppkafka-0.3.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./cppkafka-0.3.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/cppkafka-0.3.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/cppkafka-0.3.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcppkafka0.3.1-0.3.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcppkafka-devel-0.3.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

